
Automation of MySQL 

update & Upgrade Raspbian OS by the command sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade
 install Docker curl -sSL https://get.docker.com | sh
Add “pi” user to “docker” group sudo usermod -aG docker pi
check the Docker version  docker version     This command is to check whether Docker has been installed successfully or not
check the Docker Info & Errors  docker Info
edit /boot/cmdline.txt file sudo nano /boot/cmdline.txt and add two parameters: cgroup_enable=memory swapaccount=1 at the end of these lines and reboot
add Hello-world container docker run hello-world
After the docker installation, I start to create the image and container of MySQL

docker pull mysql:latest
docker image to check whether the image of mysql has been pulled successfully
docker run --name db -d -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=123 -p 3306:3306 mysql:latest
docker ps to find the ports and names of the mysql container
docker exec -it db/bin/bash
mysql username password
touch Dockerfile   ---- create a file at the desktop
vim Dockerfile

FROM mysql:latest
ENV MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD 123
ENV MYSQL_DATABASE users
ENV MYSQL_USER aminos
ENV MYSQL_PASSWORD 1234
ADD setup.sql/docker-entrypoint-initdb.d
EXPOSE 3306

docker build -t amine/mysql101
docker image --- to check whether the mysql image and container has been created successfully


References:

Spinning MySQL Database with Docker https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kOrGN36ViaU&t=2s
Apache, PHP & MySql on Docker on Ubuntu 19.04 https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w_aVnMmrASE

